 0417:     """
 0418:     Susceptible, Infected, Removed (SIkR). Method of k-stages of I
 0419: 
 0420:     .. math::
 0421:         \dot{S_{i}}=-\lambda_{i}(t)S_{i},
 0422:     .. math::
 0423:         \dot{I}_{i}^{1}=k_{E}\gamma_{E}E_{i}^{k}-k_{I}\gamma_{I}I_{i}^{1},
 0424:     .. math::
 0425:         \dot{I}_{i}^{k}=k_{I}\gamma_{I}I_{i}^{(k-1)}-k_{I}\gamma_{I}I_{i}^{k}, 
 0426:     .. math::
 0427:         \dot{R}_{i}=k_{I}\gamma_{I}I_{i}^{k}.
 0428: 
 0429:     .. math::
 0430:         \lambda_{i}(t)=\\beta\sum_{j=1}^{M}\sum_{n=1}^{k}C_{ij}(t)\\frac{I_{j}^{n}}{N_{j}},
 0431:     ...
 0432: 
 0433:     Parameters
 0434:     ----------
 0435:     parameters: dict
 0436:         Contains the following keys:
 0437: 
 0438:         beta: float
 0439:             Rate of spread of infection.
 0440:         gI: float
 0441:             Rate of removal from infectives.
 0442:         kI: int
 0443:             number of stages of infection.
 0444:     M: int
 0445:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 0446:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 0447:     Ni: np.array(M, )
 0448:         Initial number in each compartment and class
 0449:     """
 0450:

 0783:         '''The Galerkin method is defined in the TSI report, section 2.6
 0784:          It spectral accuracy in s and allows for adatptive timestepping in t
 0785:          For constant contact matrix, use 'odeint', otherise use 'Crank Nicolson'
 0786:              -Notable advantage over predictor/corrector is flexibility in time-stepping
 0787:              -Notable disadvantages include:
 0788:               (1) ill-suited to non-smooth dynamics (like most spectral methods)
 0789:               (2) must be solved as DAE when contact matrix is time-dependent (slow)
 0790:         
 0791:         For most practical purposes, we regard predictor/corrector as the preferred choice.
 0792:         '''
